      "text": "Crash between first pass and second pass: If the server\n identifies mismatched chunks and sends batch requests, \nbut the client crashes mid-transfer, how is this recovered?\n Is the batch table idempotent on retry, or can you end up \nwith duplicate data in the datastore?\nbatch has batchid (guid)\nserver exp retries\nbackground job kills all long pending jobs\n",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Crash between first pass and second pass: If the server\n identifies mismatched chunks and sends batch requests, \nbut the client crashes mid-transfer, how is this recovered?\n Is the batch table idempotent on retry, or can you end up \nwith duplicate data in the datastore?\nbatch has batchid (guid)\nserver exp retries\nbackground job kills all long pending jobs\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
