      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "raft leader election on chunk server: You mention fast reads \nand slow writes with raft. Are reads served from any replica \n(potentially stale), or only from the leader? If stale reads are \nallowed, could a backup job incorrectly conclude a chunk already \nexists when it was actually deleted/garbage-collected?\nfast w, slow r. rocks db  \nraft : easier to implement than paxos\nread from replica, 2 backups are good time apart..enough to replicate\n        no staleness***",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "raft leader election on chunk server: You mention fast reads \nand slow writes with raft. Are reads served from any replica \n(potentially stale), or only from the leader? If stale reads are \nallowed, could a backup job incorrectly conclude a chunk already \nexists when it was actually deleted/garbage-collected?\nfast w, slow r. rocks db  \nraft : easier to implement than paxos\nread from replica, 2 backups are good time apart..enough to replicate\n        no staleness***",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
